    "description": "smORFer is a small ORF (smORF) detection algorithm that integrates genome, ribosome profiling and translation initiaton stalling data. Ribosome profiling sequencing data (Ribo-Seq) generates ribosome protected fragments (RPFs) that can exactly located ribosome on mRNA. Translation initiation stalling sequencing (TIS-seq) is generated by blocking ribosomes at the start codon and subsequent sequencing of the protected fragments. Both Ribo-Seq and TIS-seq use special antibiotics to stall the ribosomes.",
